  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2015-01-07T05:00:00Z", 
    "text": "End Pay Discrimination Through Information Act\n\n Amends the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938 to revise the prohibition against employer retaliation for employee complaints. Prohibits retaliation for inquiring about, discussing, or disclosing the wages of the employee or another employee in response to a sex discrimination complaint or charge, or in furtherance of a sex discrimination investigation, proceeding, hearing, or action, including an investigation conducted by the employer."
  }, 
